---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Pug Age Calculator — Dog to Human Years"
  description="Calculate your Pug's age in human years. Pugs are a small brachycephalic breed. Accurate dog-to-human conversion using the DNA methylation formula. Free, instant."
>
  <section class="container-custom py-10 sm:py-16 md:py-24 pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-xs text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-2 sm:mb-3">
        <a href="/" class="text-[var(--text-faint)] hover:text-[var(--text-secondary)] transition-colors no-underline">Home</a>
        <span class="text-[var(--text-faint)] mx-1.5">›</span>
        <span class="text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Pug Age Calculator</span>
      </p>
      <span class="inline-block text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--text-faint)] px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-[var(--border-default)] mb-4 sm:mb-6">Breed Calculator</span>
      <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">Pug Age Calculator — Dog to Human Years</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Pugs are one of the most beloved companion breeds worldwide. As a small brachycephalic breed, Pugs age at a small-breed rate but face unique health challenges related to their flat faces. Use our Pug age calculator to find your Pug's true human equivalent age.
      </p>

      <div class="card card-hover-lift p-4 sm:p-6 md:p-8 mb-8" id="breed-calc-root">
        <form id="breed-calc-form" class="space-y-5">
          <div>
            <label for="breed-name" class="block text-sm font-medium text-[var(--text-secondary)] mb-1">Your Dog's Name <span class="text-[var(--text-faint)]">(optional)</span></label>
            <input type="text" id="breed-name" class="input-base" placeholder="e.g. Winston" maxlength="30" />
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div>
              <label for="breed-years" class="block text-sm font-medium text-[var(--text-secondary)] mb-1">Years</label>
              <input type="number" id="breed-years" class="input-base" placeholder="0" min="0" max="30" required />
            </div>
            <div>
              <label for="breed-months" class="block text-sm font-medium text-[var(--text-secondary)] mb-1">Months</label>
              <select id="breed-months" class="select-base">
                {Array.from({ length: 12 }, (_, i) => <option value={i}>{i === 0 ? '0 months' : i === 1 ? '1 month' : `${i} months`}</option>)}
              </select>
            </div>
          </div>
          <button type="submit" class="btn-primary w-full justify-center text-base py-3">🐾 Calculate Human Age</button>
        </form>

        <div id="breed-result" class="hidden mt-8 pt-8 border-t border-[var(--border-default)] text-center" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-1">Your Pug is equivalent to</p>
          <p class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-[var(--text-primary)]" id="breed-human-age">—</p>
          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-[var(--text-secondary)] mt-2">human years old</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] mt-4" id="breed-stage"></p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[var(--text-faint)] mt-2" id="breed-expectancy"></p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-block mt-6 text-sm text-[var(--color-link)] hover:underline">Try the full calculator with health timeline →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-center text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-12">
        <a href="/" class="text-[var(--color-link)] hover:underline">← Back to main Dog Age Calculator</a>
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--text-primary)]">Pug Age FAQ</h2>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-[var(--text-primary)] font-medium mb-1">How old is my Pug in human years?</h3>
          <p>Enter your Pug's age above. We use the DNA methylation formula (16 × ln(age) + 31) with a small-breed multiplier, giving you a scientifically accurate human-equivalent age based on your Pug's actual biological aging rate.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-[var(--text-primary)] font-medium mb-1">What is the lifespan of a Pug?</h3>
          <p>Pugs typically live 12–15 years. Their lifespan can be significantly impacted by weight management and respiratory health — Pugs kept at a healthy weight and monitored for breathing difficulties tend to live longer, healthier lives.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-[var(--text-primary)] font-medium mb-1">When is a Pug considered a senior?</h3>
          <p>Pugs are generally considered seniors around age 9–10. At this stage, bi-annual vet checkups are recommended, with special attention to respiratory health, weight, eye condition, and skin fold hygiene.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-[var(--text-primary)] font-medium mb-1">What health issues do Pugs face as they age?</h3>
          <p>Pugs are prone to Brachycephalic Obstructive Airway Syndrome (BOAS), eye problems (including proptosis), obesity, and skin fold infections. Their flat faces make breathing more labored, especially in heat or during exercise. Regular monitoring and weight control are essential to a long Pug life.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-[var(--border-default)] space-y-3 text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--text-primary)]">Pug Aging Guide</h2>
        <p>Pugs are a brachycephalic small breed, typically living 12–15 years. Their flat faces — while endearing — create significant health considerations that intensify with age. Understanding these challenges early helps owners give their Pug the best possible quality of life.</p>
        <p>Weight management is the single most important factor in a Pug's longevity. Obesity worsens breathing difficulties dramatically in brachycephalic breeds — even a few extra pounds can severely impact a Pug's respiratory capacity and comfort. Keep your Pug lean, avoid overfeeding, and opt for low-impact exercise like gentle walks in cool weather.</p>
        <p>Eye health monitoring is essential throughout a Pug's life. Their prominent eyes are susceptible to corneal ulcers, dry eye, and proptosis (eye prolapse from trauma). Weekly skin fold cleaning prevents bacterial and yeast infections in the facial wrinkles. As Pugs age, schedule bi-annual vet visits focusing on respiratory assessment, weight management, eye health, and skin fold hygiene.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-[var(--border-default)]">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3 text-center">More Breed Calculators</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-2">
          <a href="/labrador-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Labrador</a>
          <a href="/golden-retriever-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Golden Retriever</a>
          <a href="/german-shepherd-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">German Shepherd</a>
          <a href="/french-bulldog-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">French Bulldog</a>
          <a href="/dachshund-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Dachshund</a>
          <a href="/chihuahua-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Chihuahua</a>
          <a href="/pomeranian-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Pomeranian</a>
          <a href="/yorkshire-terrier-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Yorkshire Terrier</a>
          <a href="/rottweiler-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Rottweiler</a>
          <a href="/corgi-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Corgi</a>
          <a href="/great-dane-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Great Dane</a>
          <a href="/husky-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Husky</a>
          <a href="/shih-tzu-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Shih Tzu</a>
          <a href="/border-collie-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Border Collie</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://dogbreedage.com" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Pug Age Calculator", "item": "https://dogbreedage.com/pug-age-calculator" }
  ]
})} />

<script>
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
  const form = document.getElementById('breed-calc-form');
  const result = document.getElementById('breed-result');
  const haEl = document.getElementById('breed-human-age');
  const stageEl = document.getElementById('breed-stage');
  const expEl = document.getElementById('breed-expectancy');
  const multiplier = 0.85;
  const lifespan = [12, 15];
  const sizeLabel = 'small';
  const thresholds = [0.5,2,4,8,12,99];
  const stages = ['Puppy','Teenager','Young Adult','Adult','Senior','Elder'];

  form.addEventListener('submit', (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    const years = parseInt(document.getElementById('breed-years').value);
    const months = parseInt(document.getElementById('breed-months').value);
    const name = document.getElementById('breed-name').value.trim() || 'Your Pug';
    if (isNaN(years) || years < 0) { alert('Please enter a valid age'); return; }
    if (years === 0 && months === 0) { alert('Age must be greater than 0'); return; }
    const total = years + months / 12;
    const ha = Math.round((16 * Math.log(Math.max(total, 0.083)) + 31) * multiplier * 10) / 10;
    let stage = 'Elder';
    for (let i = 0; i < thresholds.length; i++) { if (total <= thresholds[i]) { stage = stages[i]; break; } }
    document.querySelector('#breed-result p:first-child').textContent = `${name} is equivalent to`;
    haEl.textContent = ha;
    stageEl.textContent = `Life Stage: ${stage}`;
    expEl.textContent = `Life expectancy: ${lifespan[0]}-${lifespan[1]} years`;
    result.classList.remove('hidden');
    result.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' });
  });
});
</script>
